I take it as the outward sign that i am worse. my doctor prescribes mild sedative.[he is killed off; a new doctor replaces him, prescribers a series of pharmacopeias nos. 2, 3, 4.] in time i take to smoking before i enter the tesselated field. {gardener, who so consistently tallies both his serving girls as a pair, discovers after five years that i am smokefree; he forces me to start smoking again.}
i am told (by my servant) that it has been observed that when i become smokefree i lose weight, and when i begin to acquire the redness again, i gain it.
i am treated for the afflication, the treatment giving me a new self [another philtrum (which razes away another portion of that soft & mobile area around the nose), a nose of tessarae!-that other remedy used a similar technique to effect the facelift.
